extends layout

block content
    section#main-panel
        #faq
            .text-center
                h1 Frequently Asked Questions
            #questions
                p
                    a(href='#one') How do I identify a reputable user?
                p
                    a(href='#two') Is it important to close an inquiry?
                p
                    a(href='#three') The other party declined my request to complete or abandon a job, what do I do?
                p
                    a(href='#four') What is appealing and how does it work?
                p
                    a(href='#five') Is it possible to create more than one Listings?
                p
                    a(href='#six') Are users obligated to follow the offer terms made by other party?
                p
                    a(href='#seven') How do reports work?
                p
                    a(href='#eight') How can I become a moderator/administrator for M-ploy?
                p
                    a(href='#nine') The other party stopped responding to a job that is currently active, what do I do?
                p
                    a(href='#ten') Does M-ploy handle payments between users?
                p
                    a(href='#eleven') I subscribed to the monthly plan but changed my mind, can I get a refund?
                p
                    a(href='#twelve') What are medals?
                p
                    a(href='#thirteen') I received a warning, what does it mean and how does that affect me?
                p
                    a(href='#fourteen') What are some of M-ploy's long term goals?
                p
                    a(href='#fifteen') Can I advertise other things on M-ploy other than my listing?
                p
                    a(href='#sixteen') I am banned, what did I do and is there a way to appeal it?
                .mb-5
                    .text-center If you have any other questions, you can email them to 
                        a(href='mailto:support@m-ploy.com') support@m-ploy.com
            #answers
                #one.answer-div
                    b How do I identify a reputable user?
                    .answer Reputable users can be identified by a combination of the following:
                        ul.mt-3
                            li
                                strong Completed Jobs 
                                | - The number of jobs they successfully completed.
                            li
                                strong Rating 
                                | - The 5 star rating given by other users.
                            li
                                strong Verified Reviews 
                                | - Reviews with 
                                strong Job Complete Verified 
                                | shows that the review came from a client who has completed a job with the user.
                            li
                                strong Medals 
                                | - Medals are purchased and honored to the user by other users.
                        p Be aware that low numbers should be taken into consideration as users can create alternative accounts to give them the needed factors mentioned above.
                #two.answer-div
                    b Is it important to close an inquiry?
                    .answer No. If you don't close an inquiry, you just can't submit another one to the same user and must re-use the active inquiry.
                #three.answer-div
                    b The other party declined my request to complete or abandon a job, what do I do?
                    .answer If a complete request is declined, the job stays in the 
                        strong Active Jobs
                        |  stage. If an abandon request is declined, the job is moved to the 
                        strong Abandoned Jobs
                        |  stage, where you can appeal the decision.
                #four.answer-div
                    b What is appealing and how does it work?
                    .answer When you feel the other party went against your agreement to abandon a job, you can appeal the decision. Our support team will look into your message history to see if there was an actual agreement to abandon the job. If one exists, the job will be moved to the 
                        strong Incomplete
                        |  stage.
                #five.answer-div
                    b Is it possible to create more than one Listings?
                    .answer
                        p Currently, all users are only allowed to create one listing. If you feel you have other services to offer, you can include it in your listing.
                        p M-ploy have future plans to introduce a new monthly subscription to allow multiple listings per user.
                #six.answer-div
                    b Are users obligated to follow the offer terms made by other party?
                    .answer No. The offer terms does not act as a contract between two parties. It is only used to record what the terms are. Users can use the information to create their own binding contract with their customers.
                #seven.answer-div
                    b How do reports work?
                    .answer Reports can be made against three things; reviews, users, and listings. When you click the report button, a report is sent to the administration panel for investigation. Only one report per user can be made for each of the three mentioned. When your report has reached a decision by an administrator, you can make another report again.
                #eight.answer-div
                    b How can I become a moderator/administrator for M-ploy?
                    .answer If you would like to volunteer to become a moderator for M-ploy, you can contact us and our support team will be happy to assist you through the process. From time to time, M-ploy may offer job opportunities to become an administrator. These are paid positions and can be found in the 
                        a(href='/careers') Careers
                        |  page.
                #nine.answer-div
                    b The other party stopped responding to a job that is currently active, what do I do?
                    .answer There is not much you can do if users decide to stop using M-ploy. You can contact them personally to ask for the response. Just note that, M-ploy is liable for all issues handled outside of M-ploy. See the 
                        a(href='/tos') Terms of Service
                        |  for more information.
                #ten.answer-div
                    b Does M-ploy handle payments between users?
                    .answer Currently, M-ploy does not handle payments between users. Users who are working with other users online are responsible to handle their own payments. Good news is that, M-ploy have plans in the future to implement a system to accept and release funds on behalf of users.
                #eleven.answer-div
                    b I subscribed to the monthly plan but changed my mind, can I get a refund?
                    .answer No. Refer to the 
                        a(href='/tos') Terms of Service
                        |  for more information.
                #twelve.answer-div
                    b What are medals?
                    .answer Customers who feel the user they worked with exceeded their expectations on the job can purchase a medal for the user. Medals is a way for the customer to show appreciation on a job well done and for the user to build their business reputation online.
                #thirteen.answer-div
                    b I received a warning, what does it mean and how does that affect me?
                    .answer A warning to you is not publicly displayed, so it does not impact your reputation at all. A warning is simply just a warning to you. However, if you receive many warnings for the same reason, you may receive a temporary ban.
                #fourteen.answer-div
                    b What are some of M-ploy's long term goals?
                    .answer You can read more about M-ploy's long term goals in the 
                        a(href='/about') About
                        |  page.
                #fifteen.answer-div
                    b Can I advertise other things on M-ploy other than my listing?
                    .answer Currently, you can only advertise your listing as M-ploy does not have an ad campaign system to manage advertisements.
                #sixteen.answer-div
                    b I am banned, what did I do and is there a way to appeal it?
                    .answer There are two types of ban
                        ul.mt-3.ml-3
                            li
                                strong Temporary Ban 
                                | - Temporary ban are given with a reason. You may receive temporary bans for, and not limited to the following:
                                li.ml-3 You received many warnings for the same reason.
                                li.ml-3 You were given a warning where you need to remove words/content that you submitted, but didn't do so in the given time frame.
                                li.ml-3 Suspicious account activity.
                            li.mt-3
                                strong Permanent Ban 
                                | - Permanent bans are given without a reason. You may receive a permanent ban for, and not limited to the follow:
                                li.ml-3 Fraud activities
                                li.ml-3 You violated the Terms of Service that have zero-tolerance for. See the 
                                    a(href='/tos') Terms of Service
                                    |  for more information.
                                li.ml-3 You have received three temporary bans already.
                        | Bans cannot be appealed.